  "prompt": "What are some best songs to listen to?",
  "response": "The \"best\" songs can vary greatly depending on personal taste, but here's a list of popular and critically acclaimed songs across various genres that you might enjoy:\n\n### Pop\n1. **Billie Eilish - \"Bad Guy\"**\n   - A catchy and innovative pop track with a unique style.\n2. **Dua Lipa - \"Don't Start Now\"**\n   - An infectious dance-pop song with a retro vibe.\n\n### Rock\n1. **Queen - \"Bohemian Rhapsody\"**\n   - A timeless classic known for its operatic sections and powerful vocals.\n2. **Foo Fighters - \"Everlong\"**\n   - An iconic rock anthem with intense energy and memorable guitar riffs.\n\n### Hip-Hop/Rap\n1. **Kendrick Lamar - \"Alright\"**\n   - A powerful and uplifting track with socially conscious lyrics.\n2. **Drake - \"God's Plan\"**\n   - A melodic rap song with a catchy beat and relatable lyrics.\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **Frank Ocean - \"Thinkin Bout You\"**\n   - A soulful and emotionally resonant ballad.\n2. **SZA - \"The Weekend\"**\n   - A smooth R&B track with a captivating melody.\n\n### Indie/Alternative\n1. **Arcade Fire - \"Wake Up\"**\n   - An energetic and anthemic song with a unique sound.\n2. **Lorde - \"Royals\"**\n   - A minimalist pop song with powerful lyrics and a strong beat.\n\n### Electronic/Dance\n1. **Daft Punk - \"Get Lucky\"**\n   - A funky and infectious dance track featuring Pharrell Williams.\n2. **Calvin Harris feat. Rihanna - \"We Found Love\"**\n   - An uplifting and euphoric dance-pop hit.\n\n### Country\n1. **Johnny Cash - \"Hurt\"**\n   - A haunting and emotional cover of the Nine Inch Nails song.\n2. **Chris Stapleton - \"Tennessee Whiskey\"**\n   - A soulful country ballad with a smooth vocal performance.\n\n### Jazz\n1. **Miles Davis - \"So What\"**\n   - A classic jazz piece known for its cool and relaxed vibe.\n2. **Ella Fitzgerald - \"Summertime\"**\n   - A timeless and soothing jazz standard.\n\nFeel free to explore these songs and find the ones that resonate with you the most!",
